=== Rally for Rivers ===
Rally for Rivers is a campaign launched by Isha Foundation in 2017 to tackle the scarcity of water across rivers in India and instill awareness about protecting rivers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://addieu.com/events/rally-for-rivers-our-major-rivers-are-dying-help-save-our-rivers/255/|title=Rally for Rivers}}</ref> <sup class="noprint Inline-Template " style="white-space:nowrap;">&#x5D;</sup> [[ဇဂ္ဂိ ဝသုဒေဝ်|Sadhguru]] launched the campaign on 3 September from Isha Yoga Centre, Coimbatore.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Isha Foundation launches 'Rally for Rivers' campaign in city|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/coimbatore/isha-yoga-launches-rally-for-rivers-campaign-in-city/articleshow/59519542.cms|author=Times of India}}</ref> The campaign included a month-long, nationwide campaign.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/current-affairs/140917/go-green-for-rivers-sadhguru-jaggi-vasudev.html|title=Go green for rivers: Sadhguru Jaggi Vasudev}}</ref> On 3 October, a river revitalisation draft proposal was presented by Sadhguru to Narendra Modi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Companies/QtPj7Z5lXVopc9qAKeZQ2K/Indian-economy-not-ready-for-a-startup-epidemic-Sadhguru-Ja.html|title=Indian economy not ready for a startup epidemic: Sadhguru Jaggi Vasudev}}</ref> Six states signed Memorandums of Understanding (MoU) with Isha Foundation to plant trees along river banks. These states are Karnataka, Assam, Chhattisgarh, Punjab, Maharashtra and Gujarat.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bengaluru/karnataka-isha-foundation-join-hands-to-plant-25-crore-saplings-along-riverbeds/articleshow/60446479.cms|title=Karnataka, Isha Foundation join hands to plant 25 crore saplings along riverbeds}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/environment/developmental-issues/maharashtra-to-organize-tree-plantation-conclave-to-conserve-and-protect-rivers/articleshow/60708752.cms|title=River conservation: Maharashtra to organize tree plantation conclave for awareness}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/chandigarh/people-govt-should-join-hands-to-save-dying-rivers-says-sadhguru/474807.html|title=People, govt should join hands to save dying rivers, says Sadhguru}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/assam-government-inks-mou-with-isha-foundation/articleshow/62123016.cms|title=Assam government inks MOU with Isha Foundation|author=Singh}}</ref><ref name="Times of India">{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/niti-aayog-ceo-led-group-to-study-isha-foundations-proposals/articleshow/62045210.cms|title=Niti Aayog CEO-led group to study Isha Foundation's proposals}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thehitavada.com/Encyc/2017/11/29/It-is-our-responsibility-to-hold-rainfall-and-allow-it-to-flow-365-days--Sadhguru.aspx|title=It is our responsibility to hold rainfall and allow it to flow 365 days: Sadhguru}}</ref> <sup class="noprint Inline-Template " style="white-space:nowrap;">&#x5D;</sup> The Niti Aayog and the Ministry of Water Resources have constituted committees to study the draft policy proposal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-pmo-asks-niti-aayog-to-examine-isha-foundation-s-river-revival-plan-2567199|title=PMO asks NITI Aayog to examine Isha Foundation's river revival plan}}</ref> Under the flag name of Rally for rivers, Cauvery calling campaign is being organised which would last for over a decade. this project mainly focuses on river Kaveri. In November, at a conference in Germany, the executive director of the United Nations Environmental Program, Erik Solheim discussed Rally for Rivers with Sadhguru, and how environmental programs around the world can emulate its success.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/rally-for-rivers-discussed-at-global-landscapes-forum/1216049|title=Rally for Rivers discussed at Global Landscapes Forum}}</ref>

Rally for Rivers has been criticised by environmentalist who allege that it was trying to solve a complex problem with a "shallow solution".<ref>{{Cite news|title=Indians are incapable of being fanatics|url=https://gulfnews.com/lifestyle/indians-are-incapable-of-being-fanatics-1.2162297|work=gulfnews.com}}</ref>

=== Cauvery Calling ===
The Cauvery Calling project aims to support farmers in planting an estimated 2.4 billion trees through agroforestry, thereby covering one third of Cauvery basin with trees, as a means of conserving it.

The project has received acclaim from politicians and members of the movie industry, yet environmentalists and public intellectuals have alleged that the program presents a simplistic view of river conservation, sidestepping social issues and ignoring the potential harm to tributaries and wildlife habitats.<ref name=":02">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/cauvery-calling-ngos-urge-leonardo-dicaprio-to-withdraw-support/article29511545.ece|title=Cauvery Calling: NGOs urge Leonardo DiCaprio to withdraw support}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/environment/leonardo-dicaprio-cauvery-calling-civil-society-groups|title=Civil Society Groups Ask Leonardo DiCaprio to Revoke Support for 'Cauvery Calling'}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/n-ram-questions-jaggi-vasudevs-cauvery-calling-asks-why-it-shifts-goal-posts-112838|title=N Ram questions Jaggi Vasudev's Cauvery Calling, asks why it shifts goal posts}}</ref>

A public interest litigation has also been filed in the Karnataka High Court questioning the legality of the fundraising practices for the initiative, and the usage of government owned land for a private purpose without supporting study.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livelaw.in/news-updates/-karnataka-high-court-issues-notice-on-pil-challenging-fund-collection-for-cauvery-calling-project-148186|title=Karnataka High Court Issues Notice On PIL Challenging Fund Collection For 'Cauvery Calling' Project|date=2019-09-18|work=www.livelaw.in}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/current-affairs/140919/pil-filed-against-cauvery-calling-campaign.html|title=PIL filed against Cauvery Calling campaign|date=2019-09-14|work=Deccan Chronicle}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/bengaluru/2019/sep/18/pil-to-cap-cash-collection-for-cauvery-calling-project-2035326.html|title=PIL to cap cash collection for 'Cauvery Calling' project|work=The New Indian Express}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/hc-notice-to-state-on-plea-to-examine-isha-foundations-cauvery-calling-project/article29443669.ece|title=HC notice to State on plea to examine Isha Foundation's 'Cauvery Calling' project|date=2019-09-18|work=The Hindu}}</ref> In January 2020, the High Court ruled that the Foundation needed to disclose details of its fundraising practices relating to the initiative.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Disclose details of money collected under 'Cauvery Calling': HC to Isha Foundation|work=The New Indian Express|date=2020-01-08|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/karnataka/2020/jan/08/disclose-details-of-money-collected-under-cauvery-calling-hc-2086658.html}}</ref>

== Ashram ==
Isha Foundation's headquarters are located in an ashram built on the foothills of the Velliangiri Mountains, adjacent to the Nilgiri Biosphere Reserve,<ref name="Hudson 2017 2">{{Harvard citation no brackets|Hudson|Hudson|2017}}</ref> some forty kilometres from the city of Coimbatore in the state of Tamil Nadu, South India.<ref name="berghella-69">{{Harvard citation no brackets|Berghella|2018}}</ref>

=== Adiyogi Shiva statue ===
[[ဝှာင်:IMG_j257.jpg|thumb|350x350px|Adiyogi Shiva statue, located at Isha Foundation's ashram near Coimbatore, India.]]
Sadhguru Jaggi Vasudev designed the 112-foot Adiyogi Shiva statue, which is located at the Isha Yoga Centre. It was inaugurated on Mahashivaratri, 24 February 2017, by the Prime Minister of India, Narendra Modi.<ref>{{Cite news|title=PM Narendra Modi unveils first 112-foot tall Shiva statue in Coimbatore|url=http://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/pm-narendra-modi-to-unveil-first-112-foot-tall-shiva-statue-in-coimbatore-on-mahashivratri-5-interesting-facts-to-know/563295/|publisher=[[The Financial Express (India)|The Financial Express]]|date=24 February 2017}}</ref>
The Adiyogi statue depicts Shiva as the first yogi or Adiyogi, and first Guru or Adi Guru, who offered yoga to humanity. The statue was built by the Isha Foundation using 20,000 individual iron plates supplied by the Steel Authority of India<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.covaipost.com/coimbatore/gigantic-statue-of-first-yoga-guru-adiyogi-to-be-unveiled-by-pm/|title=Gigantic statue of first yoga guru Adiyogi to be unveiled by PM|date=8 February 2017}}</ref> and weighs around 500 tonnes (490 long tons; 550 short tons). The Adiyogi Shiva Statue has been recognised as the "Largest Bust Sculpture" by Guinness World Records.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Largest bust (sculpture)|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/458751-largest-bust-sculpture}}</ref> A consecrated Shivalinga called "Yogeshwar Linga" is placed in front of the Adiyogi Shiva statue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://isha.sadhguru.org/blog/sadhguru/spot/yogeshwar-a-heartless-yogi/|title=Yogeshwar: A Heartless Yogi|publisher=Isha Foundation}}</ref>

== Controversies and reception ==
The foundation's construction activities at Isha Yoga Centre in Coimbatore are alleged to have violated rules and regulations on several occasions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/ahead-isha-foundation-s-maha-shivaratri-event-tn-forest-dept-issues-precaution-list-97734?amp|title=Forest department issues notice to Isha foundation|work=thenewsminute.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.livemint.com/Politics/RY0zSYSF8H7qe2qrtr2QfM/Chorus-grows-louder-against-Modis-visit-to-Isha-Foundation.html|title=Chorus grows louder against Modi's visit to Isha Foundation event in Coimbatore|work=Livemint}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/in-other-news/120718/cag-slams-forest-dept-for-isha-foundation-encroachments.html|title=CAG slams forest dept for Isha Foundation 'encroachments'|work=Deccan Chronicle}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/news/isha-foundation-violation-forest-land|title=CAG Slams TN Govt On ISHA Foundations Unregulated Buildings|work=The Quint}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/150419/nation-current-affairs/article/row-over-land-given-isha-foundation|title=Row over land given to Isha foundation|work=Deccan Chronicle}}</ref>

In 2016, allegations were made that Isha Yoga Centre was holding people captive. A couple claimed that their two adult daughters were being held captive at the centre.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Jaggi Vasudev's Isha Yoga Centre accused by retired professor of holding his daughter captive|work=Firstpost|url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/jaggi-vasudevs-isha-yoga-centre-accused-by-retired-professor-of-holding-his-daughter-captive-2929778.html}}</ref><ref name="Captive">{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/coimbatore/My-son-is-being-held-captive-in-Isha-Yoga-Centre-woman-says/articleshow/53603325.cms|title=My son is being held captive in Isha Yoga Centre, woman says {{!}} Coimbatore News - Times of India|work=The Times of India}}</ref> The Foundation denied the allegation and released a statement by the two women asserting that it was their free will to stay at Isha.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/isha-foundation-denies-allegations-that-yoga-center-is-holding-two-women-captive-2933280.html|title=Isha Foundation denies allegations that yoga centre is holding two women captive|work=Firstpost}}</ref> The case was dismissed in court.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Isha Foundation gets reprieve as Madras HC dismisses plea centre is holding two women captive|work=Firstpost|url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/isha-foundation-gets-reprieve-as-madras-hc-dismisses-plea-centre-is-holding-two-women-captive-2952656.html}}</ref> Another woman alleged that her adult son was being held captive at Isha Yoga Centre.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/jaggi-vasudevs-isha-yoga-centre-has-brainwashed-my-son/17509171|title='Jaggi Vasudev's Isha Yoga centre has brainwashed my son'|work=mid-day}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/isha-foundation-holding-my-32-year-old-son-hostage-claims-another-parent-47842|title=Isha Foundation is holding my 32-year-old son hostage, claims another parent|work=The News Minute}}</ref>

